  overviewText="Periodontitis — active gum disease with bone loss — requires more than a standard cleaning. Our periodontal treatment options range from non-surgical deep cleaning (scaling and root planing) and laser-assisted periodontal therapy to pocket reduction surgery, bone grafting, and soft-tissue grafting. The treatment we recommend depends on the severity of disease, the depth of gum pockets, the degree of bone loss, and which teeth are affected. Our goal in every case is to arrest the infection, create an environment you can maintain at home, and preserve as many teeth as possible."
  overviewExtra="Thrive Dental's periodontal team treats patients from Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, Little Neck, and surrounding areas who have been diagnosed with gum disease — or who suspect they have it. A significant number of adults in Queens have some degree of periodontitis without knowing it, because the disease progresses silently in its early and moderate stages. Our comprehensive periodontal exams include six-point pocket depth measurement on every tooth, digital X-ray bone level assessment, and bleeding index documentation — giving us an accurate picture of your periodontal status and a clear baseline to measure treatment success against. If you've been told you need periodontal treatment and want a second opinion, or if you're looking for a periodontally focused practice in Northern Queens, we're here."
